  "texts": [
    "That is because the location can be represented as latitude and longitude.",
    "The location offset is calculated based on geographical distance, also known as geodetic distance, which is the shortest arc length between two locations along the Earth's surface, using GeographicLib package 38.",
    "The rationale behind this metric is that it is also acceptable if a certain LLM generates a close approximation to the true value.",
    "For example, if the extracted location, in terms of latitude and longitude, is within 10 meters of the true location, we treat the result as correct.",
    "Similarly, if the extracted depth is within a range of 10 feet (∼3 meters), we would accept this extraction result."
